comments.body:
@edsantiago I could use your eyes and experience with these tests.  [A good many of them are failing](https://cirrus-ci.com/task/5979929179848704?logs=integration_test) due (apparently) `Resolved "alpine" as an alias (/etc/containers/registries.conf.d/000-shortnames.conf)` pointing at `docker.io/library/alpine:latest`.  Whereas the tests expect `quay.io/libpod/alpine:latest`. I can't find where that `000-shortnames.conf` comes from, any clue?  Also, shouldn't that be overridden by `tests/registries.conf`?  Maybe should the CI scripts just remove this file if it exists (makes me nervous)?

---

Stepping back, I believe all these changes were your recommendation (so they align with the conformance-tests and operate with more POLA).  Maybe I'm mistaken, and/or maybe these changes don't actually have much benefit?  Maybe it's okay to rely heavily on the `registries.conf` (hack?) working on into the foreseeable future and test-developers will just have to suffer?
